  "texts": [
    "We employed an LLM to semantically match the rubrics generated by our model with those labeled by human experts, calculating precision (the proportion of synthetic rubrics that were also labeled by humans) and recall (the proportion of human-labeled rubrics identified by the rubric generator).",
    "The fine-tuned model achieved an F1 score of 0.790, a significant improvement over the starting checkpoint, which had an F1 score of 0.639.",
    "RIFL requires a strong rubric verifier to provide reliable reward signals for RL.",
    "Therefore, rather than directly prompting an off-the-shelf LLM as the rubric verifier, we propose a two-stage finetuning pipeline to train a rubric verifier that can better align with expert human raters.",
    "Rubric verification data collection."
